            "title": "FedEx Freight targets up to 12% operating profit growth ahead of spinoff",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>April 8 (Reuters) - FedEx Freight set a compounded operating income growth target of 10% to 12% for the medium term, ahead of the freight trucking giant's first-ever investor day on Wednesday.</p><p>\n              The freight trucking arm of FedEx will be spun off from the delivery company on June 1 into a separate, publicly listed firm.</p><!-- Article --><p>\n              FedEx Freight, the largest provider of less-than-truckload (LTL) services in the U.S., also set a medium-term compounded revenue growth target of 4% to 6%. </p><p>\n               (Reporting by Nandan Mandayam in Bengaluru; Editing by Sahal Muhammed)</p></div>",
            "link": "https://hk.marketscreener.com/news/fedex-freight-targets-up-to-12-operating-profit-growth-ahead-of-spinoff-ce7e50dad089f124",
            "pub_date": "2026-04-08 20:45:45",
